This call stack basically indicates circular inheritance.  This was guarded 
against, but looking at the code, I can see a case involving templates where we 
will end up in this loop.  Code that looks something like the following will 
compile and not really be circular inheritance, but will look that way to the 
symbol table:

class Foo();
class Bar();
template < class T, class U> class A {};
template < class X > class A < X, X > : public A< X, Bar >
{
   typedef int TYPE;
};
template < class X > class A < X, Foo > : public A< X, X >
{
   void f ( TYPE );
};
